Project Execution Instructions
Step 0 – Download the Script

Download the project script file and save it in a local directory on your computer.

Step 1 – Install Python

Visit the official Python website:
https://www.python.org/downloads/

Download Python 3.11 or 3.12
During installation, it is very important to select the option:
	Add Python to PATH
Then click “Install Now”
Step 2 – Open Command Prompt

Open the command prompt (CMD) or terminal on your system.

Step 3 – Verify Python Installation

Run the following command to confirm that Python is correctly installed:

python -V
Step 4 – Navigate to the Project Folder

Use the command line to navigate to the directory where the script is located.

Step 5 – Create a Virtual Environment

Create a dedicated virtual environment for this project:

py -3.14 -m venv forex_env

Activate the virtual environment:

forex_env\Scripts\activate
Step 6 – Upgrade pip (Optional)

Update pip to the latest version:

python -m pip install --upgrade pip
Step 7 – Install Required Libraries

Install all necessary dependencies:

pip install yfinance pandas numpy matplotlib scikit-learn lightgbm fredapi
Step 8 – Run the Script

Once all libraries are installed, execute the script using:

python forex_predictionJoseOlmos.py
Step 9 – Deactivate the Virtual Environment (Optional)

After completing the execution, you can exit the virtual environment with:

deactivate
